The paper deals with a logical framework for reasoning about refinement relations, which is relevant to various areas of computer science such as software verification and design, and dynamic epistemic logic. The paper also presents an extension of the logic to the modal µ-calculus, which is a formalism used in computer science for specifying and verifying properties of systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
